    "created_at": "2015-04-23T15:15:56Z",
    "updated_at": "2015-04-23T15:15:56Z",
    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "Having looked at the following resources,\n\nhttp://www.w3.org/WAI/eval/Overview.html\nhttp://www.w3.org/WAI/ER/tools/\nhttp://www.w3.org/WAI/users/involving.html\nhttp://www.uiaccess.com/accessucd/ut_plan.html#recruiting\n\nThree incremental steps appear useful to make notebooks more accessible:\n1. Select and run some of the automatic evaluation tools on some representative notebooks\n2. Address the most salient accessibility issues unearthed by these tools \n3. involve users with relevant disabilities, e.g., through college programs and ask them for comments. Given the growing significance of IPython in research context there might be a chance of having some institution conduct a field study\n\nOn 1.: The easiest starting-point would be some editible notebooks online as test candidates. There should be a webapp providing this. Any hint? - Or can someone set up a test environment offline?\n\nLeo \n"
  },
