    "author_association": "CONTRIBUTOR",
    "body": "A few easy changes:\n\n![screenshot from 2015-04-23 23 14 58](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/599274/7312333/9c48af8c-ea0e-11e4-8a50-cfec5dcdfbbc.png)\n\n1 . The `select` elements need to have labels:\n\n![screenshot from 2015-04-23 23 15 48](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/599274/7312362/c789cf6e-ea0e-11e4-8f26-77b10c158043.png)\n\n2 . The text in the menus needs to have better contrast:\n\n![screenshot from 2015-04-23 23 17 11](https://cloud.githubusercontent.com/assets/599274/7312371/f5016614-ea0e-11e4-8db1-7f18a08a2be3.png)\n\n3 . When navigating using the tab key, when we reach a cell in the notebook, the focus goes to that cell immediately and is not possible to move to other cells.\n\n4 . Explicit use of tabindex. The default is working okay but I remember it is not possible to navigate through modals.\n\nThis stuff is really really important particularly if you're receiving funding from agencies that require accessibility in software. It wouldn't be a bad idea to talk to a lawyer about this.\n"
